time required: 15 minutes
servings: 2
---

Boil a large #pot{} of water for the pasta. Add @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Chop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{} widthways into 3 pieces.

Cook the tenderstem in the boiling water for ~{1%minute}. Remove the tenderstem from the water but keep the water for the pasta.

Cook the @Orecchiette pasta{200%g} in the water for ~{10%minutes}. Reserve 4 tbsp of the pasta water then drain.

Heat a #frying pan{} up on medium high heat. Add in the @pine nuts{1%tbsp} and toast them for a few mins.

> Watch the nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Remove and keep to the side.

Heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, cut open the
@Pork & Oregano Sausage{1} and cook the meat in
the pan (discard the skins). Cook for around ~{5%minutes} until nicely browned off.

Add the tenderstem and @Chilli Flakes{1/4%tsp} and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @ground black pepper{a few grinds}.

Add 4 tbsp of reserved pasta water then add the pasta. Add @Green Pesto{1.5%tbsp} and stir.

Serve with a sprinkle of pine nuts.